Author

STAT 245 Fall 2024

Response variable

Fit a regression model using as your response variable: number of bird species present.

Data Access

You can find your data at: https://sldr.netlify.app/data/island-birds.csv

Context

This dataset was recently analyzed by Yuhao Zhao and colleagues in the paper Land-use change interacts with island biogeography to alter bird community assembly.

The researchers state,

[Human] activities have reshaped biodiversity on islands worldwide. However, it remains unclear how island attributes and land-use change interactively shape â¦ island biodiversity â¦ To answer this, we conducted bird surveys in various land-use types (mainly forest and farmland) using transects on 34 oceanic land-bridge islands in the largest archipelago of China. We found that bird species richness increased with island area and decreased with isolation, regardless of the intensity of land-use change. However, forest-dominated habitats exhibited lower richness than farmland-dominated habitats. Island bird assemblages generally comprised species that share more similar traits â¦ than expected â¦ Contrary to our expectations, we observed that bird assemblages in forest-dominated habitats were more clustered on large and close islands, whereas assemblages in farmland-dominated habitats were more clustered on small islands. Our findings â¦ suggest that agricultural landscapes on large islands may play essential roles in protecting countryside island biodiversity.

Can you replicate some of the studyâs findings with your analysis?

Variables in the dataset include:

  • Location variables, transect_ID and island_ID. Each transect is within one island.
  • species_richness: the number of distinct bird species that were found on this transect
  • island_area in log\(_{10}\)(hectares). Measure of island size.
  • isolation, kilometers from nearest other island
  • func_dist: a relative measure of how similar the bird species present are, based on features of the birds such as body length, body mass, bill length, wing length, tail length, and others
  • phyl_dist: a relative measure of how similar the bird species present are, based on their evolutionary relatedness
  • mean_HWI: the mean hand-wing index of the bird species present. This index measures the birdâs ability to disperse (flying potential to reach a new, maybe far away habitat).
  • farmland_cover, forest_cover, and settlement_cover measure land use. They give the proportion of the transect that is farmland, forest, and human settlements.
  • main_land_use tells whether a greater proportion of the land use is for âfarmâ or âforestâ.
